{"title":"Paladin","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Paladin","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n*This article is about the obsolete player class. For the monster, see [Paladin (monster)](/Paladin_\\(monster\\) \"Paladin (monster)\").*\n\n**Paladins** are holy warriors who worship [the Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\"), and share many abilities of the [Fighter](/Fighter \"Fighter\") and the [Priest](/Priest \"Priest\"). In particular, they are charged with smiting evil, and gain power from destroying demons, the undead, and other evil beings.\n\nNote that a Paladin's religion requires them to fight honorably. They must refrain from using [poison](/Poison \"Poison\"), unholy magic or items, or attacking while [invisible](/Invisibility \"Invisibility\"). Nor can they attack a confused, held, fleeing, sleeping, paralyzed, or otherwise helpless opponent, unless that opponent is evil. Of course, you may deem [the Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\")'s protection and gifts to be more than worth all this restraint.\n\nPaladins begin with 28 [piety](/Piety \"Piety\").\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Racial Restrictions](#Racial_Restrictions)\n- [2 Starting Equipment](#Starting_Equipment)\n- [3 Starting Skills](#Starting_Skills)\n- [4 History](#History)\n\n## Racial Restrictions\n\nAs with other religious classes, [demigods](/Demigod \"Demigod\") cannot be Paladins. In addition, the undead races ([mummies](/Mummy \"Mummy\"), [ghouls](/Ghoul \"Ghoul\"), and [vampires](/Vampire \"Vampire\")) and [demonspawn](/Demonspawn \"Demonspawn\") may not start as Paladins, since [the Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\") will not accept them as followers. Even temporarily becoming undead via the [Necromutation](/Necromutation \"Necromutation\") spell will result in excommunication.\n\n[Humans](/Human \"Human\"), [high elves](/High_elves \"High elves\"), [mountain dwarves](/Mountain_dwarves \"Mountain dwarves\"), [hill orcs](/Hill_orc \"Hill orc\"), [centaurs](/Centaur \"Centaur\"), and [minotaurs](/Minotaur \"Minotaur\") are the recommended races for this class.\n\n## Starting Equipment\n\n- Paladins start with a +0 [falchion](/Falchion \"Falchion\"), +0 [ring mail](/Ring_mail \"Ring mail\"), +0 [shield](/Shield \"Shield\"), [potion of healing](/Potion_of_healing \"Potion of healing\"), and a [bread ration](/Bread_ration \"Bread ration\"), before racial variation.\n\n## Starting Skills\n\nAdjusted for species aptitudes:\n\n- [Fighting](/Fighting \"Fighting\") 2\n- [Long Blades](/Long_Blades \"Long Blades\") 3\n- [Shields](/Shields \"Shields\") 2\n- [Armour](/Armour_\\(skill\\) \"Armour (skill)\") 2\n- [Invocations](/Invocations \"Invocations\") 2\n\n## History\n\nPaladins were removed in [0.8.0](/0.8.0 \"0.8.0\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Paladin - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Paladin\",\"wgTitle\":\"Paladin\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":68418,\"wgRevisionId\":68418,\"wgArticleId\":107,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Obsolete articles\",\"Obsolete backgrounds\",\"Backgrounds\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",